Installation Instructions
========================

Prerequisites:
  - Python 3.8 or later
  - pip (Python package installer)

Quick install:

  ./configure
  make
  make install

This installs ytran to /usr/local/bin by default.  To change the prefix:

  ./configure --prefix=$HOME/.local
  make
  make install

To uninstall:

  make uninstall

API Keys:

  ytran expects two API key files.  Create these before running ytran.

  1. Anthropic API key (~/.anthropic_api_key)

     Sign up at console.anthropic.com, go to API Keys, and create a key.
     Save it:

       echo 'sk-ant-...' > ~/.anthropic_api_key
       chmod 600 ~/.anthropic_api_key     # read/write for you only

  2. Transcript API key (~/.youtubetotranscript_api_key)

     Sign up at transcriptapi.com, copy your bearer token from the
     dashboard.  Save it:

       echo 'your-token-here' > ~/.youtubetotranscript_api_key
       chmod 600 ~/.youtubetotranscript_api_key

  The chmod 600 sets permissions to -rw-------, meaning only your user
  can read or write the file.  Without this, other users on the system
  could read your API keys.  Never use 644 or 755 for secret files.
